HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 225
BY REPRESENTATIVE ECHOLS
A RESOLUTION
To urge and request the Louisiana Department of Environmental Quality, the Governor's
Office of Homeland Security and Emergency Preparedness, the Ouachita Parish
Police Jury, and the municipalities within Ouachita Parish to jointly study a
parish-wide solid waste, debris removal, and disaster resiliency service model; to
evaluate consolidation of services; to explore public-private partnerships and funding
mechanisms; and to report findings and recommendations to the Legislature of
Louisiana.
WHEREAS, Ouachita Parish includes multiple municipalities and unincorporated
areas currently utilizing separate solid waste collection, debris removal, and cleanup
systems, resulting in fragmented services, inefficiencies, and inconsistent disaster response
capacity; and
WHEREAS, Louisiana routinely experiences hurricanes, floods, ice storms,
tornadoes, and other natural disasters that generate massive volumes of storm debris
requiring rapid and coordinated removal and disposal which often must also comply with
procedures of the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA); and
WHEREAS, parish-wide coordination of trash service, vegetative debris collection,
construction and demolition waste management, and emergency cleanup operations can
improve efficiency, reduce taxpayer costs, enhance resiliency, and expedite disaster
recovery; and
WHEREAS, many communities across the United States have successfully
implemented consolidated solid waste authorities or regional service districts that provide
one-stop shop solutions for routine trash service, disaster debris response, recycling, landfill
operations, and mitigation planning; and
